President Obama will host the final White House Science Fair of his Administration, celebrating student competitors and winners from STEM competitions. He will call on this generation of students to tackle challenges such as climate change and space exploration. The President will highlight the importance of STEM education and announce new initiatives to support it, including new guidance from the Department of Education, a $200 million investment from Oracle to support CS education, and commitments from over 500 K-12 schools to expand access to CS. The President also emphasizes the need to incorporate STEM into early childhood education and to provide opportunities for underrepresented groups in STEM. Additionally, over 100 organizations are announcing new commitments to support CS education, including partnerships to train teachers and expand access to CS, a new online matching platform to connect STEM professionals with volunteer opportunities, and commitments to expand STEM learning for young learners.